<pre><code> byte[] byteArray = getIntent().getByteArrayExtra("image");
Bitmap bmp = BitmapFactory.decodeByteArray(byteArray, 0,byteArray.length); 
</code></pre>
<p>While this is not the best practice to do this task with the perspective of performance, you should save the image in your disk first and fetch it through file path. </p>
